Package: ooacquire
Type: Package
Title: Acquire Spectral Data from Ocean Optics Spectrometers
Version: 0.1.0
Date: 2015-08-10
Author: Pedro J. Aphalo <pedro.aphalo@helsinki.fi>
Maintainer: Pedro J. Aphalo <pedro.aphalo@helsinki.fi>
Description: Functions to acquire data directly from the spectrometer,
    apply corrections and calibration to obtain either counts per
    second or spectral irradiances. It targets Ocean Optics Maya2000Pro
    but algorithms and code should be directly applicable to other
    USB-connetced spectrometers from Ocean Optics.
License: GPL (>=2)
VignetteBuilder: knitr
Depends:
    R (>= 3.2.0),
    photobiology (>= 0.8.8),
    photobiologygg (>= 0.4.0),
    photobiologyWavebands (>= 0.3.3)
Roxygen: list(wrap = FALSE)
Imports:
    rOmniDriver (>= 0.1.6),
    dplyr (>= 0.4.3),
    Rcpp (>= 0.12.1),
    caTools (>= 1.17.1),
    lubridate (>= 1.3.3)
Suggests:
    knitr  (>= 1.11),
    ggplot2 (>= 1.0.1)
LinkingTo: Rcpp
Bytecompile: yes
NeedsCompilation: yes
LazyLoad: yes
LazyData: yes
Encoding: UTF-8
URL: http://www.r4photobiology.info,
    https://bitbucket.org/aphalo/mayacalc
BugReports: https://bitbucket.org/aphalo/mayacalc
